# PAM service file for `regind`'s web UI login (FEAT-087, acceptance
# criterion 12). Installed at /etc/pam.d/regin.
#
# Uses pam_unix.so directly (not `@include common-auth`/`common-account`)
# since those includes only exist on Debian-family systems with
# libpam-runtime — this package ships for deb/rpm/apk alike (see
# packaging/nfpm.yaml), so the service file has to work without them.
# Defers to each host's local user/password database; adjust locally
# (e.g. add pam_access.so to require a specific group) if "any local
# login-capable user" is too broad for a given deployment.
auth     required   pam_unix.so
account  required   pam_unix.so
